{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σπόγγος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>sponge</b>, σ. πολυτρήτοισι τραπέζας νίζον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.111, compare 22.439; σπόγγῳ ἀμφὶ πρόσωπα καὶ ἄμφω χεῖρ᾽ ἀπομόργνυ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.414; ὑγρώσσων σ. ὤλεσεν γραφήν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1329 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; used at the bath, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 55, 5th c.BC: Crates Comicus 15.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; for cleaning shoes. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 600 (compare σπογγίζω);compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 487b9, 588b20, NT.Matt.27.48, etc. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>any spongy substance</b>, σικυώνης σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Steril.” 221\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ σ. the <b>glands</b> in the throat, <b>tonsils</b>, from their <b>spongy</b> nature and liability to swell, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Epid.” 4.7, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 19.140. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> ={νήριον}, Ps.-[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 4.81\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]. (<b>σφόγγος</b> is found in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 11 (2). 144 A 37 (Delos, 4th c.BC), “PSI” 6.558.7 (3rd c.BC), “POxy.” 1384.25 (V 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; compare σπογγιά, σπογγίον.)","strongNumber":"G4699","accentedUnicode":"σπόγγος","shortDef":"sponge","mediumDef":"<b>a sponge,</b> <ref='Mat.27.48'>Mt. 27:48</ref>; <ref='Mrk.15.36'>Mk. 15:36</ref>; <ref='Jhn.19.29'>Jn. 19:29</ref>*","stepGloss":"sponge","stepTransliteration":"spongos","count":3,"_es_Definition":"esponja","_zh_tw_Definition":"海綿","_zh_Definition":"海绵","_step_Type":"w